articles.description: Cam Ward scored 14 points and Drew Urquhart and Everett Duncan added 13 each as Vermont defeated New Hampshire 71-58 on Thursday night for the Catamounts' 15th consecutive victory.
articles.headline: Vermont beats UNH 71-58 for 15th straight victory

articles.description: Vasa Pusica scored 17 of his 24 points in the first half and Anthony Green tied a career-high with 16 points as Northeastern held off Drexel 75-69 on Thursday night for its fourth straight win.
articles.headline: Pusica's big first half helps Huskies hold off Dragons

articles.description: Garrison Mathews had 17 points as Lipscomb got hot in the second half to beat Stetson 82-73 to win its third straight in Atlantic Sun Conference play on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Lipscomb gets hot in 2nd half, beats Stetson 82-73

articles.description: Tyler Nelson scored 29 points with three 3-pointers, Ferron Flavors Jr. added 16 points with four 3s and grabbed 10 rebounds, and Fairfield held off Marist 83-79 on Thursday night to end a two-game skid.
articles.headline: Nelson scores 29, Fairfield holds off Marist 83-79

articles.description: Shep Garner drills his third 3-pointer of the night and his cousin, Flavor Flav, is loving it.
articles.headline: Garner's 3 gets Flavor Flav up from his seat

images.caption: Shep Garner drills his third 3-pointer of the night and his cousin, Flavor Flav, is loving it.
images.name: Garner's 3 gets Flavor Flav up from his seat

articles.description: Ethan Happ had 21 points and 12 rebounds, and Wisconsin secured its biggest win of a challenging season, beating No. 6 Purdue 57-53 on Thursday night.
articles.headline: Happ's double-double leads Wisconsin over No. 6 Purdue

images.caption: Brad Davison puts the Badgers up 49-46 late in the second half with a sweet step-back jumper.
images.name: Davison drains clutch step-back
